  <sect2 role="installation">
    <title>Installation of Ncurses</title>

    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2003/XInclude"
    href="../common/ncurses.xml"
    xpointer="xpointer(//*[@role='installation']/para[1])"/>

    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2003/XInclude"
    href="../common/ncurses.xml"
    xpointer="xpointer(//*[@role='installation']/screen[1])"/>

    <para>The Ncurses package will use the environment variables
    <envar>CC</envar> and <envar>CXX</envar> in preference to variables
    you may pass to the configure script. To force Ncurses to use our
    build flags we temporarily set <envar>CC</envar> and
    <envar>CXX</envar>:</para>

<screen><userinput>export CC="${LFS_TARGET}-gcc ${BUILD32}"
export CXX="${LFS_TARGET}-g++ ${BUILD32}"</userinput></screen>

    <para>Prepare Ncurses for compilation:</para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/tools --with-shared \
   --host=${LFS_TARGET} --without-debug --without-ada \
   --enable-overwrite --with-build-cc=gcc</userinput></screen>

    <xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2003/XInclude"
    href="../../final-system/common/ncurses.xml"
    xpointer="xpointer(id('install-gettext')/variablelist[1])"/>

    <para>Compile the package:</para>

<screen><userinput>make</userinput></screen>

    <para>Install the package:</para>

<screen><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <para>Now restore your original environment variables:</para>

<screen><userinput>source ~/.bash_profile</userinput></screen>

  </sect2>

